You hear the distant call of a hawk,<break time="2.5s"/> circling high above,<break time="2s"/> and somewhere deeper in the forest,<break time="2s"/> the soft trickle of water over stone.<break time="3.5s"/>

The Shekinah Restorer walks beside you now,<break time="2.5s"/> her presence like warm sunlight on your skin.<break time="3s"/>
She whispers,<break time="2s"/> not in words,<break time="2s"/> but in felt-sense,<break time="2.5s"/> reminding you that you are held,<break time="2s"/> that you belong here,<break time="2s"/> that what has been fragmented within you is being gently gathered together.<break time="4s"/>

You continue forward,<break time="2s"/> and the path begins to descend,<break time="2.5s"/> winding down through ferns and moss-covered rocks,<break time="2.5s"/> until you arrive at a clearing.<break time="3.5s"/>

